---

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

import ResumePDF from '../../public/assets/resume.pdf';

import routes from '../global/routes';

---

<Layout title="About Me | Atish">
	<main class="container mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 max-w-6xl">
		<section class="py-16 md:py-24">
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-8">
				About Me
			</h1>
			<p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
				Hi there! I'm Atishaya, but honestly, everyone just calls me Atish. I'm that person who gets way too excited about graph theory proofs and can spend hours debugging code just to make a website pixel-perfect.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-6">
				My Story
			</h2>
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-300 p-8 rounded-sm">
					<p class="text-base md:text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed mb-6">
						I grew up in Nepal and somehow ended up in Winnipeg, Canada (trust me, the weather was quite the adjustment!). Currently, I'm working on a Joint Honours degree in Mathematics and Computer Science with a minor in Statistics at the University of Manitoba.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base md:text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
						If you need my resume, you can grab it <a href={ResumePDF} target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 font-bold hover:underline transition-all duration-200">here</a>. Want to chat? Hit me up through my <a href={routes.contact} class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 font-bold hover:underline transition-all duration-200">contact page</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-6">
				What Gets Me Excited
			</h2>
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<p class="text-base md:text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
					If you couldn't tell already, I'm pretty obsessed with mathematics. There's something beautiful about how abstract concepts can solve real-world problems. My favorite areas are probably <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory" target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 hover:underline">Graph Theory</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_complexity_theory" target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 hover:underline">Computational Complexity Theory</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorics" target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 hover:underline">Combinatorics</a> – basically the stuff that makes your brain hurt in the best possible way.
				</p>
				
				<div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-300 p-8 rounded-sm">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-6">
						What I'm Working On
					</h3>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-3">Day Job</h4>
							<p class="text-base text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
								I work as a Frontend Developer at <a href="https://alpiniststudios.com" target="_blank" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 font-bold hover:underline">Alpinist Studios</a>, where I help build and maintain LG US' website. It's pretty cool getting to work on something that millions of people actually use.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-3">Research (The Fun Stuff)</h4>
							<p class="text-base text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed mb-4">
								I'm lucky enough to be doing research in three different labs. 
							</p>
							<p class="text-base text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed mb-4">
								With the mathematics department, I'm diving deep into k-nary trees and something called the HK-property with Dr. Mahsa Nasrollahi-Shirazi and Dr. Andrii. It's related to the famous <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erd%C5%91s%E2%80%93Ko%E2%80%93Rado_theorem" target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 hover:underline">Erdős–Ko–Rado theorem</a> but restricted to <a href="https://xlinux.nist.gov/dads/HTML/perfectBinaryTree.html" target="_blank" class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 hover:underline">perfect binary trees</a>.
							</p>
							<p class="text-base text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
								On the theoretical algorthims side, I'm working with the <a href="https://home.cs.umanitoba.ca/~gada/" target="_blank" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 font-bold hover:underline">GADA lab</a> under Dr. Stephane Durocher. We're working on approximation algorithms for spatially embedded graphs, which is a fancy way of saying we're trying to make sense of complex networks in a more manageable way.
							</p>
							<p class="text-base text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed mt-4">
								And finally, I'm also doing some research in the <a href="https://terrabyte.acs.uwinnipeg.ca/" target="_blank" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 font-bold hover:underline">Computer Vision Lab</a> with Dr. Christopher Henry, 
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-6">
				Where I'm Headed
			</h2>
			<div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-300 p-8 rounded-sm">
				<p class="text-base md:text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
					The goal is to eventually get a PhD – probably in Computer Science or Mathematics (still figuring that one out). I love the idea of spending even more time diving deep into research and maybe teaching along the way.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-100 mb-6">
				When I'm Not Nerding Out
			</h2>
			<div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-300 p-8 rounded-sm">
				<p class="text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed">
					I'm probably out taking long walks (great for thinking through tough problems), biking around the city, reading, or experimenting in the kitchen. I have a serious weakness for traditional Nepali food – especially anything with rice. Rice is honestly the best food ever invented.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 font-regular leading-relaxed mt-6">
					I also really enjoy teaching and helping people figure out tricky concepts, especially when it comes to programming or math stuff that I struggled with myself. There's something really satisfying about that "aha!" moment when things finally click.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
